title: Left/right sound balance
summary: Not used for calls.

title: Mono audio
summary: Play the same sound out of both speakers.

title: Remove animations
summary: Prevent some screen effects. Useful if you're sensitive to animation or screen movement.

title: Accessibility button
summary: None

title: Side and Volume up keys
summary: None

title: Volume up and down keys
summary: None

title: Speak keyboard input aloud
summary: Characters

title: Voice Label
summary: Write voice recordings to NFC tags to provide you with information when you're nearby. The tags are purchased separately and can be associated with objects or locations you use regularly.

title: Hearing aid compatibility
summary: Adjust your phone's audio so it works better with hearing aids.

title: Universal switch
summary: Use external accessories to control your phone and select items on the screen.

title: Assistant menu
summary: Show a menu of easy-to-reach buttons that let you replace hardkeys, gestures, and other common interactions.

title: Wave hand to turn on screen
Interaction control
summary: Block touches for the Back, Home, and Recents buttons, the keyboard, and a selected area of the screen.

title: Tap duration
summary: Set how long an interaction needs to be held to be recognized as a tap.

title: Ignore repeated touches
summary: Set a time within which to ignore repeated touches.

title: Sticky keys
summary: When you press a modifier key like Shift, Ctrl, or Alt, it will stay pressed so you can enter keyboard shortcuts one key at a time.

title: Slow keys
summary: Type by touching and holding for a set time to avoid accidental key presses.

title: Bounce keys
summary: Prevent accidental key presses by setting a delay before a second tap on the same key is accepted.

title: Ignore diagonal movements
summary: This can help prevent accidental skipping to a different line of text.

title: Move with cursor while typing
summary: Move the Magnifier window as you type. Not supported in all apps.

title: Select apps to show contextual menus with
Replace swipe with single tap
summary: Respond to alarms, alerts, and incoming calls by tapping instead of swiping.
